Subject: [PATCH 64/71] video: da8xx-fb: adopt pinctrl support

This commit comes from branch ti-linux-3.12.y:
  git://git.ti.com/ti-linux-kernel/ti-linux-kernel.git

Update da8xx-fb driver to set the state of the pins to:
- "default on probe & resume
- "sleep" on suspend

By optionally putting the pins into sleep state in the suspend callback
we can accomplish two things.
- minimize current leakage from pins and thus save power,
- prevent the IP from driving pins output in an uncontrolled manner,
which may happen if the power domain drops the domain regulator.

Signed-off-by: Hebbar, Gururaja <gururaja.hebbar@ti.com>
CC: detheridge@ti.com
Signed-off-by: Dave Gerlach <d-gerlach@ti.com>
Signed-off-by: Darren Etheridge <detheridge@ti.com>
(cherry picked from commit 7b436ecf87773343bedcc0b62ec635bda8e8308c)
Signed-off-by: Zumeng Chen <zumeng.chen@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/video/da8xx-fb.c |    6 ++++++
 1 files changed, 6 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/video/da8xx-fb.c b/drivers/video/da8xx-fb.c
index add76fe..a57bdcf 100644
--- a/drivers/video/da8xx-fb.c
+++ b/drivers/video/da8xx-fb.c
@@ -1834,6 +1834,9 @@ static int fb_suspend(struct platform_device *dev, pm_message_t state)
 	pm_runtime_put_sync(&dev->dev);
 	console_unlock();
 
+	/* Select sleep pin state */
+	pinctrl_pm_select_sleep_state(&dev->dev);
+
 	return 0;
 }
 static int fb_resume(struct platform_device *dev)
@@ -1841,6 +1844,9 @@ static int fb_resume(struct platform_device *dev)
 	struct fb_info *info = platform_get_drvdata(dev);
 	struct da8xx_fb_par *par = info->par;
 
+	/* Select default pin state */
+	pinctrl_pm_select_default_state(&dev->dev);
+
 	console_lock();
 	pm_runtime_get_sync(&dev->dev);
 	lcd_context_restore();
